  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The announcement of the overthrow of the government of Alhaji Shehu Shagari was done by General Sani Abacha&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The announcement of the overthrow of the government of General Mohamadu Buhari Buhari was made by Brig. Joshua Dongoyaro.<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The chairman of the military Tribunal that tried those alleged to be involved in 1997 coup in Nigeria was Victor Malu.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The chairman of the military tribunal that tried those alleged to be involved in 1995 coup involving Olusegun Obasanjo and Shehu Yar&rsquo;Adua was Patrick Aziza&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Leader of April 22, 1990 military coup in Nigeria was Major Gideon Okar. The coup was the bloodiest coup in Nigeria.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Leader of the first military coup in Nigeria (Jan 15th 1966) was Major Chukwuma Kaduna Nzeogwu&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The chairman of National Interim Government set up by President Ibrahim Babangida in August 1993 was Chief Ernest Shonekan&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The former USSR disintegrated\/ dissolved into 15 independent states in 1991&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first multi-racial election was held in South Africa in 1994&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The world smallest independent state is Vatican City State and was established in 1929. Its form of government is papal commission&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Obasanjo, Thabo Mbeki, Abdelaziz Boute Flika, Abdoulaye Wade and Hosni Mubarak were pioneers of NEPAD &lsquo;&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Taiwan was expelled from UNO and replaced with China&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In 1995, Mozambique a Portuguese speaking country joined Commonwealth but was not colonized by Britain.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In 1961, South Africa was suspended from Commonwealth because of its apartheid policy &#39;&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In 1847, Liberia became the first Independent African state, it was colonized by the USA&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">English revolution took place in 1688&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">French revolution took place in 1789&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Russian revolution took place in 1917&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Chinese revolution took place in 1949&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Fascism was practised in Italy between 1922-44 and in Germany between 1933-45&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The military head of state in Nigeria that took the title president was president Ibrahim Babangida&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The office of Prime Minister was created in Nigeria in 1957&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first African country to become a Republic was Ghana&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Lagos became a crown colony in 1861&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">President Shehu Musa Yar&rsquo;Adua of Nigeria died on May 5, 2010 after an illness.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Political Bureau set up by Babangida regime in 1986 was headed by Prof. Sam Cookey&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first Nigerian ambassador to Britain and USA was Taiwo Matthew Mbu&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">On May 18, 2004, a state of emergency was declared in Plateau State and Major General Chris Ali was appointed sole administrator of the state by Federal Government under the leadership of President Olusegun Obasanjo.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">On October 19, 2006, a state of emergency was declared in Ekiti State and major general Tunji Olurin was appointed the sole administrator.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">In 1962, a state of emergency was declared in the Western Region and Moses Majekodumi was appointed the sole administrator. That was the first time a state of emergency was declared in Nigeria.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">On January 31, 2012, a state of emergency was declared in some local government areas in Borno State, Plateau State, Yobe State and Niger State as a result of the activities of Boko Haram that engage in bomb attack of Christians, civilians and security forces.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The countries that gave supports to Biafra during the Nigerian-Biafra War 1967-1970 include: South Africa, Rhodesia (Zimbabwe), Portugal, Zambia, Tanzania, Ivory Coast (Cote d&rsquo;Ivoire), Haiti, France, Israel, Gabon.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The countries that supported Nigeria include; Russia (the former USSR), Chad, Cameroon, Egypt, USA, and Britain.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first Chairman of Economic and Financial Crime Commission in Nigeria (EFCC) was Nuhu Ribadu.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">On May 6, 2010, Dr Goodluck Jonathan was sworn in as the president of Nigeria following the death of President Shehu Musa Yar&rsquo;Adua on 5th May 2010.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The chairman of the National Population Commission that conducted the 2006 population census in Nigeria was Chief Sumaila Makama.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A state or country that experiences constant military intervention in politics is described as praetorian state.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Nelson Mandela of South Africa was born on 18th July, 1918 and was imprisoned in 1963 for his opposition against apartheid policy. Apartheid policy in South Africa was abolished during the regime of Dr Klerk, who was the last imperial president of South Africa.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Stephen Bantu Biko was the founder of Black Conscious Movement in South Africa to oppose apartheid regime&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Idi Amin Dada, known as the butcher of Uganda for his brutal, despotic rule as president of Uganda came into power on 25th January, 1971 where he overthrew the government of Milton Obote, while Obote was attending Commonwealth meeting in Singapore.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Idi Amin Dada was overthrown in 1979 through the assistance of Tanzanian army.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n  <p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Jomo Kenyatta was the first president of Kenya. He was the author of a book entitled Facing Mounting Kenya.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "CURRENT AFFAIRS AND IMPORTANT FACTS (1)"
}